label: Book of hours (Dutch), LTK 289

metadata.label: Content
metadata.value: Dutch translation/adaptation by Geert Grote. - Also contains a calendar for the diocese Utrecht (ff. 1r-12v). - Empty: uncounted leaf between ff. 12 and 13.

metadata.label: Note
value: Origin: (Holland, northern part) based on the style of the decoration (pen-flourished initials and border decoration), the grisailles were probably made in the Southern Netherlands.
Binding: Medieval binding, contemporary. - Leather (brown, blind-tooled) over wooden boards with bevelled edges. Decorated with panel stamp on both sides (Madonna) with text "Ave gra(tia)
Also described by MMDC and A.W. Byvanckgenootschap (database RKD, The Hague).
